      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why W-Containing Words Are Versatile Scoring Tools</h2>
      <p>W is one of the most flexible mid-value tiles in Scrabble. At 4 points, it adds meaningful value to any word while being common enough in English to fit into hundreds of plays. W appears most naturally at the start of words (WILLOW, WIDOW, WAYWARD, WALLOW) but also works beautifully in the middle (BEESWAX, JIGSAW, POWWOW, SHADOW, SWALLOW) and occasionally at the end (ELBOW).</p>
      <p>The real power of W comes from its partnerships. W plus X creates BEESWAX (19 pts) — one of the highest-scoring W words available. W plus J gives you JIGSAW (17 pts). Double-W words are another strong avenue: POWWOW (17 pts), WAYWARD (17 pts), WILLOW (12 pts), and WALLOW (12 pts) all use two W tiles for efficient rack management. The WH- prefix (WHERE, WHILE, WHEAT) and -OW ending (ELBOW, SHADOW, WILLOW) provide reliable patterns you can build around whenever you draw W.</p>

